wikipedia_page.main: Brian Caine (born 20 June 1936) is an English former professional association football goalkeeper. His six siblings all played football, but he was the only to appear at a professional level. Caine started his career as an amateur with Accrington Stanley, before joining Blackpool and later Coventry City. In 1961, he signed for Barrow, and went on to play over 100 league games for the club.
